<div id="review_3691378093" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3691378093" />
    <a title="Graham" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1760824-graham"><img alt="Graham" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1380743323p2/1760824.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3691378093?book_show_action=true">Dec 17, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Graham" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Graham" href="/user/show/1760824-graham">Graham</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780340158173" href="/book/show/1450162.The_Moon_s_a_Balloon">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1760824-graham?shelf=biography-inc-auto">biography-inc-auto</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1760824-graham?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1760824-graham?shelf=cinema-and-tv">cinema-and-tv</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3691378093" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10304651405609932690">A very enjoyable autobiography from one of Britain&apos;s most beloved film stars. I remember Niven popping up in the Roger Moore autobiography I read a few years ago; there, he was the aged and ailing Hollywood star, while in this one he&apos;s the youthful figure who enters a strange industry. The first thing I should say about this book is that it&apos;s very funny, with humorous anecdotes on every page, and genuine wit throughout. The early passages, dealing with Niven&apos;s school days and army career, are pa</span>
  <span id="freeText10304651405609932690" style="display:none">A very enjoyable autobiography from one of Britain's most beloved film stars. I remember Niven popping up in the Roger Moore autobiography I read a few years ago; there, he was the aged and ailing Hollywood star, while in this one he's the youthful figure who enters a strange industry. The first thing I should say about this book is that it's very funny, with humorous anecdotes on every page, and genuine wit throughout. The early passages, dealing with Niven's school days and army career, are particularly well-developed, and the tale actually loses a little something when it reaches Hollywood and the 1950s, when things start to get rushed. There's a lot of unashamed shoulder-rubbing and name-dropping along the way, but the author makes no bones about that. I enjoyed it so much that I look forward to reading the second volume, BRING ON THE EMPTY HORSES, in due course.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10304651405609932690" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


