        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer136837770" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18096632070298529879">An amusing memoir of the first half of David Niven&apos;s life. However, there is WAY too much military stuff, that I admit I really really quickly skimmed through. Also, one gets the sense that behind the gentlemanly air and self-deprecating humor, David Niven was not a nice person, with little respect for women and definitely someone who used others to rise to the top. Articles I&apos;ve read about him since his death seem to confirm this.<br/><br/>I&apos;ve also found his second book, &quot;Bring on the Empty Horses,&quot; whi</span>
  <span id="freeText18096632070298529879" style="display:none">An amusing memoir of the first half of David Niven's life. However, there is WAY too much military stuff, that I admit I really really quickly skimmed through. Also, one gets the sense that behind the gentlemanly air and self-deprecating humor, David Niven was not a nice person, with little respect for women and definitely someone who used others to rise to the top. Articles I've read about him since his death seem to confirm this.<br /><br />I've also found his second book, "Bring on the Empty Horses," which focuses more on his movie career, and I've been told that it's a much funnier book that drags less.</span>
