<div id="review_1063316538" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1063316538" />
    <a title="Gareth Evans" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4276748-gareth-evans"><img alt="Gareth Evans" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1063316538?book_show_action=true">Sep 24, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gareth Evans" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gareth Evans" href="/user/show/4276748-gareth-evans">Gareth Evans</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1063316538" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1534939303177542445">This book has a terrific reputation; I am not sure why it fell so flat with me. It&apos;s certainly funny at times, occasionally laugh out loud funny. The sections on his military service are good, especially his pre-war service. Apart from this the book is superficial and self serving. It seems that half the book is pretty pointless name dropping - I spent lots of time with Churchill but I can&apos;t remember a word he said, etc. ad nauseum. The emotional tone of the book is very flat. A tragic death see</span>
  <span id="freeText1534939303177542445" style="display:none">This book has a terrific reputation; I am not sure why it fell so flat with me. It's certainly funny at times, occasionally laugh out loud funny. The sections on his military service are good, especially his pre-war service. Apart from this the book is superficial and self serving. It seems that half the book is pretty pointless name dropping - I spent lots of time with Churchill but I can't remember a word he said, etc. ad nauseum. The emotional tone of the book is very flat. A tragic death seems no more moving than the list of people that attended a party or swam in his pool. <br /><br />Fun at times, but very boring at others. Suave and sophisticated and a bit of a dick? The latter methinks.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1534939303177542445" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


